node.text:
I'm back again to focus on perfecting your form for different exercises, within my programs on the @Sweat app! 🤩
This form check is for a nice combination movement, the ‘Bent Leg Sit Up & Reach’, which sounds a lot more complicated than it actually is 🤣

SO, how do we start! Think of it as three movements put together, a bent leg sit up 👉 hip thrust 👉reach!!

First, let's just master doing a hip thrust, supported up by your arms. For this exercise, make sure that you are hands are facing BACKWARDS, away from your body, to create that tabletop position. Next, the bent leg sit up - which I'm sure we have all done before! Make sure that your core is engaged, and you are slowly rolling yourself up, without straining your neck. 

Now, let's put that all together to make one movement, and add that REACH at the end 🙋‍♀️

So bent leg sit up 👉 hip thrust 👉reach! And there you have it, new exercise perfected 🙌🙌 

Let me know if these form checks are helpful #SWKCommunity! 

#SweatwithKayla #SWK #SWKcommunity #SweatCommunity #Workout #SweatMade #ExerciseForm

node.title: HOW TO - BENT LEG SITUP & REACH

node.text:
Loved chatting to these three amazing Sweat trainers about their new programs yesterday on @Sweat's IG live! I especially loved that I finally got to introduce you all to Sweat's newest trainer, Monica! 💛

We spoke about all things HIIT, why we love it and what each new program is about! We also chatted a little about what #SweatMade means to us, as well as launched a SWEAT COMPETITION giving you the chance to WIN one of 20 spots to a virtual training session with all four of us trainers 🔥! Take a listen to find out more and stay tuned across @Sweat's Instagram for the details on how to enter! 

More info: get.sweat.com/sweat-made

@ChontelDuncan, @BritanyWilliams, @trainwithmon - thanks for taking the time to chat with us! 🌟

If you want to try any of our new programs, download @Sweat using the 7 day free trial today!

www.kaylaitsines.com/CardioandAbs

#SWK #SWKcommunity #SweatCommunity #Sweat #workout #HIIT #HIITWorkout #SweatMade #Competition

In this episode of my 'How To' series, I show you exactly how to set up AND dismantle the squat rack! 🏋️‍♀️

Now if you think this piece of equipment is VERY intimating... you're definitely not alone! I'm sure there's a lot of women that avoid using the squat rack when they are in the gym... and that is exactly why I have started this video series. 

BUT I want you to take me with you to the gym next time, and give yourself the time to get comfortable using the Squat Rack. And if you still feel uncomfortable, bring a friend to the gym with you so you can both learn how to use this machine together.... I promise it's not as intimidating as it looks! 🙂

This machine is used in my new High Intensity Strength Program, so if you love this machine OR if you've never used it before and want to start - I recommend my new and improved gym program for you! You can try it today by downloading @Sweat via the link in my bio! 

www.kaylaitsines.com/HighIntesnityStrengthWithKayla

#SWK #SWKCommunity #SweatCommunity #Workout #GymWorkout

node.text:
In episode 3 of of my 'How To' series, I'm showing you exactly how to set up and use a resistance band! 😄

There are so many types of resistance bands that can be used for many different exercises, but I want to show you how you can attach longer resistance bands to a bar to help you with things like assisted pull-ups and chin-ups!

You will usually find resistance bands hanging up around the gym, or you can bring your own to ensure you've got the right size available for you. ✔️

The key thing to remember with resistance bands is that the THICKER bands have MORE resistance than the thinner bands. In the case of a pull-up or chin up, the thicker band will assist you more (as there is more resistance) making it easier for you to pull yourself up to complete the exercise.

However, in most other cases (like resistance band tricep extensions or bicep curls) the thinner resistance bands actually make the exercise easier than the thicker ones! And if this confuses you a little bit, don't worry! You will instantly feel the difference and know which one is right to use when you try them out. 😅

I hope this video gives you the confidence to try an assisted pull-up or chin-up next time you are in the gym! I have included these in my new High Intensity Strength Program, which you can try by downloading @Sweat today! 

#SWK #SWKcommunity #SweatApp #SweatCommunity #gym #gymworkout

www.kaylaitsines.com/HighIntensityStrengthWithKayla

Episode ✌️ of my 'How To' series is all about how to use the Cable & Pulley machine! 
This machine can look quite intimidating at first because there are so many parts to it. I've heard my clients say that they used to walk up to the machine and use whatever attachment is already there because they are too scared (or don't know how) to change them... which I totally understand.

Hopefully, this video will help you gain the confidence to firstly... use this machine, and secondly... use the machine exactly the way you want to! So next time you're in the gym, take me with you and give yourself the time to learn how these parts actually work. I promise it's easier than you have imagined! 😊

My High Intensity Strength program includes the use of this machine, and the @Sweat app will tell you exactly which attachment you need to complete the exercise which should help you build confidence, too! You can try my new gym program today via the link in my bio 😊

PS. All the videos that I will be sharing over the next week have been filmed before Adelaide's current lockdown. Stay safe ❤️

node.text:
INTRODUCING MY NEW 'HOW TO' SERIES - GYM EDITION 🌟
As gyms begin to re-open around the world, I want everyone to feel confident and comfortable getting back to their gym-based workouts.

I also know a lot of women feel intimidated about going to the gym, especially when it comes to using large equipment... so it's for these reasons I want to show you exactly HOW TO navigate a gym setting. In this series, I'll be taking you the step-by-step process as to how to set up and use different equipment around the gym.

To kick the series off, we're starting with the equipment that was requested most by YOU, #SWKCommunity...  THE LEG PRESS! 

We have a variety of gym-based programs in the @Sweat app that involves using the Leg Press, including my new and improved High-Intensity Strength program. So, next time you're in the gym... I want you to take me with you and allow yourself the time to get comfortable with using these bigger machines. Before you know it, you'll wish you stopped avoiding them sooner! 

I hope by the end of this episode you feel a lot LESS intimidated and a lot MORE empowered to use this machine in your training. 

If you're keen to start using the Leg Press in your workouts, I recommend trying my new and improved High Intensity Strength program. It uses larger machines, free weights and bodyweight exercises to help women get fitter and get stronger! You can try it today for free using @Sweat's 7-Day free trial (link in bio)!

It has been great to bring you even more new gym programs to Sweat and from now on we will be working with @iFIT to help deliver even more choice and variety to you all!

#SWK #SweatwithKayla #SWKCommunity #SweatCommunity #LegPress #gym #gymequipment #gymtutorial

node.text: Let’s do this!! Take me anywhere with you and let’s train abs together !! (No equipment) EXPRESS WORKOUT

"But Kayla, I don't have time to workout today!!" 
... are you sure about that?! 🤣🤣

If this sounds like you, I'm here to tell you that there is almost ALWAYS time to squeeze in a workout! You just have to start telling yourself that any amount of time working out it's worth it! 
 
I've created this 5-minute "follow-along" lower body workout that should have you breaking a sweat and feeling accomplished in a short amount of time! I'm ready to work out with you right now, but it's up to YOU to set aside the time to get your body moving today! 

✅ Squat Pulse - 20 secs
- Rest for 10 secs

✅ Curtsey Lunge - 20 secs
- Rest for 10 secs

✅ Glute Bridge Walkout - 20 secs
- Rest for 10 secs

 Do 3 laps

✅ Squat Pulse finisher - 30 secs

I certainly felt the burn after that!! Did you? 🔥😅

If you love the thought of an express workout - there are SO many incredible programs in the @Sweat app that are ready and waiting for you! Head to the link in my bio for a 7-Day free trial and get moving today!

www.kaylaitsines.com/SweatwithKayla

node.text:
Are your glute bridges actually working your glutes? Or just hurting your lower back? 🤔
Glute bridges are one of those exercises that look quite easy to do... but they can hurt the wrong muscles if done incorrectly! 

I've noticed that some people push their hips as high as they can, causing them to over-extend and put pressure on their lower back. If this sounds like you, or you haven't been feeling the burn in your glutes when doing glute bridges, I want you to watch this video and practice my number one tip! 

You should absolutely be feeling your glutes burn if you do this! 🔥
Let me know if this has helped you!

www.kaylaitsines.com/SweatWithKayla

node.text:
This is an easy one to get wrong ❌ 
So if you do Ab Bikes often, I want you to take the time to learn how to get them right! ✅

In this video, I break down the exercise into smaller steps to help you perfect your form. Once you've mastered each movement, add each step in until you build up to a full Ab Bike! 

Here are some do's and don'ts to remember:
DO
✅Rest hands in front of ears
✅Rotate at the torso
✅Bring knees in close to the chest
✅Extend your legs in a push and pull motion
✅Elevate your shoulders

DON'T
❌Pull your neck up with your hands behind your head
❌Do small in and out motions with your legs
❌Curve your back away from the floor

What other exercises do you want to learn from me? Comment below!

www.kaylaitsines.com/SweatwithKayla

#SWK #SWKcommunity #Exercises #BBG #SweatwithKayla

node.text:
I'm back again to focus on perfecting your form for different exercises, within my programs on the @Sweat app! 🤩
This form check is for a nice combination movement, the ‘Bent Leg Sit Up & Reach’, which sounds a lot more complicated than it actually is 🤣

SO, how do we start! Think of it as three movements put together, a bent leg sit up 👉 hip thrust 👉reach!!

First, let's just master doing a hip thrust, supported up by your arms. For this exercise, make sure that you are hands are facing BACKWARDS, away from your body, to create that tabletop position. Next, the bent leg sit up - which I'm sure we have all done before! Make sure that your core is engaged, and you are slowly rolling yourself up, without straining your neck. 

Now, let's put that all together to make one movement, and add that REACH at the end 🙋‍♀️

So bent leg sit up 👉 hip thrust 👉reach! And there you have it, new exercise perfected 🙌🙌 

Let me know if these form checks are helpful #SWKCommunity! 

#SweatwithKayla #SWK #SWKcommunity #SweatCommunity #Workout #SweatMade #ExerciseForm

node.text:
SO. TRUE. 🙌
I’ve always loved the saying ‘comparison is the thief of joy’, because it is so accurate!! I think we can sometimes get so caught up in comparing ourselves to other people and their successes, that we can feel a bit negative towards ourselves. We get caught up in people’s highlight reels on social media, and this can affect our own insecurities. 

But EVERYONE has insecurities, including me!! Everyone is on a different path and a different journey, and no two people are the same. At the end of the day, YOU should be your only benchmark! You can’t change what other people have or do, but you can change what YOU do!! 

So, focus on YOU. Strive to be the best version of yourself every single day 🧡

#SWK #SWKCommunity #SweatCommunity #Motivation #Quote #Confidence #SweatMade

JUST IN CASE YOU NEEDED THE REMINDER TODAY (and any other day) 👇👇👇
💥There is NO such thing as a GIRL push up or a “man” push up. They are only called push ups, no differences!! 

💥The free weights section at the gym is NOT the “boys section” - it’s for absolutely everyone and anyone. And if you aren’t sure how to use a piece of equipment, just ask!! We have all started somewhere, and there are no silly questions 🙌 I’ve done a few “How-To’s” about gym equipment, so check my IGTV section if you need some extra help. 

💥Weights will NOT make you bulky!! And countering that, cardio won’t make you “thin”. 

💥You DON’T need to spend hours and hours at the gym, and you also don’t need to go every single day!! Fitness shouldn't be a chore, so find an option that you enjoy, and that suits YOU and your lifestyle. For example, my HIIT Cardio & Abs program is my preferred style of training because it's only 3 x 30 minute workouts per week, and I find that a lot more manageable and sustainable for me! 

💥You are allowed to REST!! I can be very guilty of this too, but if your body needs a rest - let it!! Listen to your body and take time when you need to. 

Got that reminder? GOOD! 👏👏 . . . and now carry on with your day 😝

#SWK #SWKCommunity #SweatCommunity #SweatMade #Sweat #Fitness #Exercise #Beach #Motivation

node.text:
FACT OR CAP - TRYING A BANDED PUSH-UP HACK I SAW ON TIKTOK 😮
Ok . . . wait a sec!! THIS WORKS!! 🤩 (And if you can’t tell by my face I am very happy that it actually did 🤣🤣)

I saw this on TikTok and HAD to try it, because it just seemed way too good to be true 😝

This is a great hack if you are trying to transition from modified push ups on your knees, to doing push ups on your toes 🙌 It works in a similar way to how resistance bands work when you are trying to practice pull ups!! You can even use different resistance strengths like you would in a resistance band pull up. 

All you have to do is put your arms inside the loop of the resistance band, and bring just above elbow height (so it doesn't affect your range of movement). Then once you start doing your push ups, it acts like a support and assists you in performing the movement!

So, this hack is a YES from me!! 👏👏

#SWKCommunity, do you have a hack like this that you can share with the community? Share below so I can keep trying out these awesome ideas!! 

#SweatwithKayla #SWK #SWKcommunity #SweatCommunity #Workout #SweatMade #Fitness #Workout

Shining the #SweatMade spotlight on Josephine (@sweat.joey.sweat)!! You absolutely are STRONG - and strength doesn't just mean what weight you can lift at the gym! The #SweatCommunity is such an amazing place to connect with other women, and I love hearing how empowering you are to each other 💛💛 Josephine has a seriously incredible list of @Sweat programs that she has accomplished, proving that hard work, dedication and the strength to keep going really pays off!

From Josephine: “I am STRONG!!!
I have endured sweat, blood and tears; and I am still HERE! And I am UNSTOPPABLE! I’ve pushed my limit and I’m still progressing. Sometimes big wins, sometimes small wins. Sometimes even a fall back; but I am STRONG so I march on.

I am strong not only to carry my own weights but to also carry the weights of those of my loved ones; for I am a wife, a mother, a daughter, a sister, a teacher, a student. I am a WOMAN! And THAT is my #superpower.

I know damn well where I get my daily strength from; my #SweatSisters!!! Always supporting each other, cheering on each other, empowering one another. We are indeed #SweatMade. When we are surrounded with so much energy, love and positivity, we can only become stronger; for ourselves, for others, and for each other. Love you so much, my queens #SweatSisters”

YES!! This message is EVERYTHING! 💪 So proud of you and the strength that you have worked so hard towards!! Keep sharing your #SweatMade stories everyone, it has been SO awesome to see!! 

Can't wait to get #SweatMade? Try a 7 day FREE trial of the @Sweat app today by heading to the link in bio!

Josephine is #SweatMade. Are you?

node.text:
CORE STRENGTH ISN'T EVERYTHING, BUT IT IS IMPORTANT! 🙌
When you think about all the activities you do in a day - sitting at a computer, chasing after a toddler, cooking dinner... your core is always supporting you without you even knowing it. 

Just like when you think about all the exercises you do when you work out... they pretty well ALL require some level of core strength.

My favourite thing about core strength is that the stronger your core is, the easier other exercises become, too!  Take this exercise for example. Some people may look at it and think "this is a lower-body exercise", but actually, it is designed primarily to target your core through functional movement. Which is my favourite way to train! ✔️

So this is why my new Cardio & Abs program has a large focus on full-body movements to work your abs. Yes there are sit-ups, ab bikes and toe-taps... but you'll be pleasantly surprised when you start to realise all of the other exercises in my program are also helping you strengthen your core, too! 

If a stronger core is what you're looking for, then my new HIIT Cardio & Abs program is for you! 😊

Try it for free for 7 days via link in my bio today. You can cancel @Sweat's free trial at any time, but I know if you're going to love it.

node.text:
Nothing better than a good sunrise!! 🙌
I’m definitely an early riser and morning person! It's so nice and quiet in the mornings, and I find that especially in summer I prefer an earlier morning workout before the heat of the day really starts to set in! These sunrises are both from where I live in Adelaide in @southaustralia - how beautiful are they?? Just another reason why I love my hometown so much! ❤️ 

I'll normally set my alarm for about 6:00am, so I can get up, wake Arna, and either get a walk or a workout in before I start my day. I will always start my day with coffee (non-negotiable, otherwise I can't function 😝), and breakfast - which is usually some form of toast, tomatoes and anchovies!

I love waking up early because it can get so much done before the day feels like it has even really started. But the downside of being an early riser is that I'm ready to go to sleep at about 9pm 😴 

So tell me #SWKCommunity - are you an early bird like me, or are you a night owl? 😴 

#SWK #SWKCommunity #SweatCommunity  #Sunrise #Sunet #Beach #SweatMade #Morning #Sunshine #SeeSouthAustralia #SeeAustralia Pic: @tahliaharvey
